decks.notes: The main focus of this deck is to control the game by utilizing a combination of counterspells, removal spells, and disruptive creatures. Geist of Saint Traft serves as the commander, providing a quick clock with its angel token, while also being protected by creatures like Mother of Runes and Stoneforge Mystic. The deck also includes a variety of powerful planeswalkers like Jace, the Mind Sculptor and Elspeth, Knight-Errant to provide additional card advantage and board presence. With a mix of permission spells like Force of Will and Mana Leak, along with removal spells like Swords to Plowshares and Path to Exile, this deck aims to disrupt the opponent's game plan while establishing its own threats for victory.

This deck focuses on using Karlov of the Ghost Council's ability to gain life and grow bigger, while also utilizing a mix of removal spells and powerful creatures to control the board and pressure the opponent. The key strategy is to gain life consistently through various sources like lifelink creatures, and then use that life gain to power up Karlov and trigger abilities that can dismantle the opponent's game plan. By mixing aggressive threats with disruptive spells, the deck aims to gain an advantage through attrition and overwhelming the opponent with a combination of efficient removal and resilient threats. The goal is to outvalue and outpace the opponent while maintaining control of the battlefield and steadily increasing the pressure on them.

This deck focuses on utilizing the aggro strategy with two partner commanders in WRG colors, Sidar Kondo of Jamuraa and Tana, the Bloodsower. The deck includes a variety of creature ramp cards, removal spells, and key combo pieces like Goblin Bombardment and Blasting Station for damage output. The main goal is to overwhelm the opponent with a wide board of creatures and utilize powerful cards like Triumph of the Hordes and Purphoros, God of the Forge to finish off the game quickly. Additionally, the deck includes a toolbox of utility creatures like Eternal Witness and Reclamation Sage to provide flexibility and answer different threats. The mana base is designed to support the aggressive nature of the deck with a mix of dual lands and mana dorks for efficient ramp.

The key strategy of this deck is to overwhelm the opponent with aggressive creatures and burn spells, with Zurgo Bellstriker as the commander leading the charge. The deck includes a variety of low-cost and efficient creatures like Goblin Guide and Monastery Swiftspear, along with powerful burn spells like Lightning Bolt and Thunderous Wrath to finish off the opponent quickly. Cards like Chandra, Pyromaster and Sarkhan, the Dragonspeaker provide additional burn and card advantage to keep the pressure on. The goal is to maintain a fast-paced tempo, utilizing haste and direct damage to close out the game before the opponent can establish their own strategy.

This deck focuses on controlling the game through a combination of counterspells, burn spells, and tempo plays. Jori En, Ruin Diver rewards the player for casting multiple spells each turn, encouraging a low-to-the-ground strategy with cheap spells that can be cast efficiently. The deck includes a variety of direct damage spells like Lightning Bolt and Burst Lightning to control the board and finish off opponents. Counterspells like Force of Will and Mana Leak provide protection while cards like Snapcaster Mage and Delver of Secrets offer card advantage and versatility. The goal is to disrupt the opponent's game plan, while steadily building card advantage and threatening the opponent's life total with efficient spells.

This deck revolves around utilizing Maelstrom Wanderer's ability to cascade into powerful spells while controlling the board with various removal, counterspells, and disruptive effects. The deck aims to ramp up quickly with mana accelerants like Orcish Lumberjack and Sakura-Tribe Elder, then cast Maelstrom Wanderer to cascade into high-impact threats like Balefire Dragon and Wurmcoil Engine. The deck also includes disruptive spells like Jokulhaups and All Is Dust to reset the board if needed. By combining powerful creatures with board control and disruption, this deck aims to outvalue and outmaneuver opponents in a 1 vs 1 Duel Commander format, creating a challenging and dynamic play experience.

The main strategy of this deck revolves around controlling the game through a combination of removal spells, discard effects, and board wipes. Skithiryx, the Blight Dragon serves as a powerful finisher, able to quickly take out opponents once their resources have been depleted. The deck includes a variety of versatile removal spells such as Murder, Hero's Downfall, and Damnation, as well as numerous hand disruption effects like Thoughtseize, Inquisition of Kozilek, and Duress. Additionally, the deck has access to powerful tutors like Demonic Tutor and Diabolic Tutor to find key pieces when needed. The mana base is optimized for black mana production, with key lands like Cabal Coffers and Urborg, Tomb of Yawgmoth providing additional mana acceleration.

The deck focuses on utilizing Venser, Shaper Savant as the commander to control the game through various bounce spells, counter magic, and extra turn effects. It aims to disrupt the opponent's strategy by countering key spells, bouncing threats back to hand, and taking extra turns to advance its own game plan. With a mix of powerful control cards like Cryptic Command, Force of Will, and Cyclonic Rift, along with efficient card draw and manipulation like Brainstorm and Serum Visions, the deck seeks to outvalue and outmaneuver opponents. Additionally, the inclusion of versatile creatures like True-Name Nemesis and Vendilion Clique provide additional ways to disrupt the opponent's plans while maintaining board presence.
